ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Pull to sit - no head lag
Prone - pivots in circle using arms
Sitting - can recover toy behind him
Stands at furniture - lifts one foot at a time
Climbs on and off adult-sized chair without help
Pedals tricycle / walks on tip toes
Up stairs 1 foot per step, down 2 feet per step
Sits up without help of hands
Walks backwards along straight line (10 paces)
Molteno Adapted Scale - Gross Motor Ceiling Value
Molteno Adapted Scale - Gross Motor Score (Developmental Age)
Molteno Adapted Scale - Gross Motor Developmental Quotient
Molteno Adapted Scale - Gross Motor Diagnosis
Notes: 0=Normally developing; 1=Borderline delay; 2=Mild delay; 3=Moderate delay; 4=Severe delay; -444= Missing

ElementDescription: Hands to mouth as voluntary act
Fingers one hand with other when lying quietly
Retains only 1 cube in hand at a time
Holds car and ''explores'' with index finger
Complete simple formboard with reversal (trial and error)
3 piece formboard with reversal (no trial and error)
Copies square with x in it
Molteno Adapted Scale - Fine Motor Ceiling Value
Molteno Adapted Scale - Fine Motor Score (Developmental Age)
Molteno Adapted Scale - Fine Motor Developmental Quotient
Molteno Adapted Scale - Fine Motor Diagnosis
Notes: 0=Normally developing; 1=Borderline delay; 2=Mild delay; 3=Moderate delay; 4=Severe delay; -444= Missing

ElementDescription: Object permanences - looks after dropped object
Object permanences - finds cube under cover
Definition by use (uses telephone and spoon)

Molteno Adapted Scale - Communication Score (Developmental Age)
Molteno Adapted Scale - Communication Developmental Quotient

Notes: 0=Normally developing; 1=Borderline delay; 2=Mild delay; 3=Moderate delay; 4=Severe delay; -444= Missing

ElementDescription: Sits on parents' knee and looks at books
Co-operative play - leadership and division of labor

ElementDescription: Molteno Adapted Scale - Global Developmental Quotient

Notes: 0=Normally developing; 1=Borderline delay; 2=Mild delay; 3=Moderate delay; 4=Severe delay; -1= N/A insufficient GDQ data; -444= Missing
